          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-05-24 14:10:39" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:ἀγαπάω&lt;SDBG:ἀγαπάω:000000&gt;}[a] ‘to love,’ {D:25.43}) pertaining to one who or that which is loved</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>object of one’s affection</Gloss>
                <Gloss>one who is loved</Gloss>
                <Gloss>beloved</Gloss>
                <Gloss>dear</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is also possible to understand ἀγαπητός in {S:04001201800016} as ‘the only beloved one’ (see {D:58.53}), and the meaning may, in fact, be simply ‘only’ or ‘unique.’ This meaning has evidently arisen because of the association of ἀγαπητός with {L:μονογενής&lt;SDBG:μονογενής:000000&gt;} ‘unique, only’ ({D:58.52}).</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
